<% @title = 'LivePipe&trade; : Download &amp; Contribute' %>
<%= header 'Download &amp; Contribute' %>
<% paragraph do %>You can clone the latest version of LivePipe UI from GitHub with the following command:<% end %>
<% css do %>git clone git://github.com/syntacticx/livepipe-ui.git<% end %>
<ul>
	<li><a style="font-size:16px;" href="http://github.com/syntacticx/livepipe-ui/tarball/master">Download Latest Tarball</a></li>
	<li><a href="http://github.com/syntacticx/livepipe-ui/tree/master">GitHub Repository</a></li>
	<li><a href="http://github.com/syntacticx/livepipe.net-documentation/tree/master">Documentation Repository</a></li>
</ul>

<% paragraph 'Submitting Issues &amp; Patches' do %>LivePipe UI uses <a href="http://github.com/syntacticx/livepipe-ui/issues">GitHub as its issue tracker</a>. You have to <a href="https://github.com/signup/free">sign up first</a> to open a new issue. Please keep the title concise and use <a href="http://github.github.com/github-flavored-markdown/">appropriate text formatting</a> for the body of the issue. Please link to <a href="http://gist.github.com/">gists</a> for patches, or check your changes into your clone on GitHub and create a pull request. <strong>The issue system is for bug reports and feature requests only.</strong><% end %>

<% paragraph 'Discussion Groups' do %><% end %>
<ul>
	<li><a href="http://groups.google.com/group/livepipe">LivePipe UI Core</a> - Patches, releases and development of LivePipe UI. <strong>Do not post support questions.</strong></li>
	<li><a href="http://groups.google.com/group/livepipe-ui-users">LivePipe UI Users</a> - Support, general questions, announcements and general discussion.</li>
</ul>
